WEBVTT

00:01:28.863 --> 00:01:31.319
So people would take them off
and throw them away.

00:01:31.343 --> 00:01:35.223
It wasn't until the turn of the nineteenth
into the twentieth century

00:01:35.247 --> 00:01:39.868
that book jackets could be seen
as interesting design

00:01:39.892 --> 00:01:41.479
in and of themselves.

00:01:41.503 --> 00:01:43.959
Such that I look at that and I think,

00:01:43.983 --> 00:01:45.489
"I want to read that.

00:01:45.513 --> 00:01:47.179
That interests me."

00:01:47.203 --> 00:01:51.427
The physical book itself represents
both a technological advance

00:01:51.451 --> 00:01:54.309
but also a piece of technology
in and of itself.

00:01:54.333 --> 00:01:57.119
It delivered a user interface

00:01:57.143 --> 00:02:00.809
that was unlike anything
that people had before.